  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chorizo-orzo-with-lemon-aioli/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roll your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chorizo-orzo-with-lemon-aioli/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!), a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>in a bowl – this is your<strong> lemon aioli</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix </strong>in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chorizo-orzo-with-lemon-aioli/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chorizo </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until crisped</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chorizo-orzo-with-lemon-aioli/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once crisped, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and <strong>pepper strips</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chorizo-orzo-with-lemon-aioli/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>orzo</strong> and stir to coat the grains in the spices, then add the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong> to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through (stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chorizo-orzo-with-lemon-aioli/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, stir through your <strong>blanched peas</strong> and cook<strong> </strong>for a further 1 min or until warmed through – this is your <strong>Spanish-style chorizo orzo</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Add half your blanched peas to a colander,</span></strong> <strong><span class=\"text-danger\">pour boiled water all over them to refresh them and leave plain!</span></strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chorizo-orzo-with-lemon-aioli/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Spanish-style chorizo orzo</strong> with the<strong> lemon aioli</strong> on the top and garnish with the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>and a <strong>lemon</strong> <strong>wedge</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave off the aioli and chopped parsley or just add a little!</span></strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Serve the refreshed peas to the side</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
